def: One who admires; one who esteems or loves greatly. Cowper.
The timber forming the ridge of a roof, into which the raftersare secured.
A valuable kind of pear, of an obovate shape and with meltingflesh of delicious flavor; -- more properly called White Doyenn√©.[Written also virgaloo, vergalieu, vergaloo, etc.]
A set or circle of persons who meet familiarly, as for social,literary, or other purposes; a clique. "The queen of your coterie."Thackeray.
To get under or beneath; also, to understand. [Obs.] R. ofGloucester.
A large blackfish seaweed (Agarum Turneri), the frond of whichis punctured with many little holes.
To strike with repeated blows for punishment; to flog; to whipor conquer, as in a pugilistic encounter. [Colloq. or Low] Carlyle.Thackeray.
In an obedient manner; with obedience.
That which is deposited beneath something else.
A quicksand.Quenched in a boggy syrtis, neither sea Nor good dry land. Milton.
A wanton woman; a courtesan. Sir T. Herbert.
To flower, or cause to flower, again. Sylvester.
